29/11/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic said on Friday (November 27th) that he is optimistic his country will progress towards NATO membership before the end of this year.
After meeting Thursday with NATO Secretary-General Anders Fogh Rasmussen, Djukanovic told reporters he thinks Montenegro will get a NATO membership action plan next month.
Late Thursday, the government's press office issued a statement quoting Rasmussen as saying NATO should stick to its open door policy for new candidates.
(RTCG, RTS, AFP, B92, FoNet - 27/11/09)
